extensions.name: Developer
extensions.description: Built-in developer extension providing core development capabilities including file operations, shell commands, and IDE integration
extensions.installation_notes: This is a built-in extension that comes with Goose by default. No installation required.

extensions.name: Non-developer
extensions.description: Built-in extension for non-developer users providing basic system interaction capabilities
extensions.installation_notes: This is a built-in extension that comes with Goose by default. No installation required.

extensions.name: Google Drive
extensions.description: Built-in Google Drive integration for accessing and managing Google Drive files
extensions.installation_notes: This is a built-in extension that comes with Goose by default. Can be accessed via goose://extension?cmd=goosed&arg=mcp&arg=google_drive&description=google_drive deeplink.

extensions.name: Memory
extensions.description: Built-in memory system for maintaining conversation context and storing information
extensions.installation_notes: This is a built-in extension that comes with Goose by default. No installation required.

extensions.name: JetBrains
extensions.description: Built-in JetBrains IDE integration supporting code reading, editing, debugging and build error detection
extensions.installation_notes: This is a built-in extension that comes with Goose by default. Can be accessed via goose://extension?cmd=goosed&arg=mcp&arg=jetbrains deeplink.

extensions.name: Block Codesearch
extensions.description: Internal code search extension for searching across Block's codebase

extensions.name: Fetch
extensions.description: Web content fetching extension with support for reading web pages and respecting robots.txt
extensions.installation_notes: Install using uvx package manager. Note: Some sites may block access via robots.txt.
